<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">The thing that has failed to be mentioned thus far is the inante power of the Druid.  I have a Bard AND a Druid.  There is no way to compare the two in the arena of Kiting.  A druid is without a doubt the best kiter in the game.  This is due to several factors.<p>

Snare is unrivaled for slowing a Mob and allowing the caster to do his damage from a distance.<p>

Level 44 Druid DoT Drifting Death does 650 damage in a minute for a measly 200 mana.<p>

Level 49 Druid spells Starfire and Ice do 612 damage.  Level 39 Firestrike does 298 damage at level 43.<p>

I have seen Magicians and Wizards 4 levels higher than myself die while trying to kill a MoB that I destroyed without a scratch.  They don't have snare, and root normally breaks after one or two DD spells are cast.<p>

Am I slamming Bards?  NO.  Am I slamming Necros?  NO.  I have one of each, and both are efficient kiters and soloers.  But Druids are still the third most powerful class in the game, as far as dealing damage is concerned.<p>

Kirov</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
