<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">yeah, druids can kite the best -- root burn simply put..<br>
 but i would like to say thati am a lvl 12 barbarian shaman and i like to solo yelow or red calfs out on the tundra in EF.  first i buff,, Sow and all the melee buffs at my disposal, then i spot my prey somewhere down by OneGuard and pull with Taintedbreath then run like a WOLF then i stop and cast sicken and run in a big circle while i watch its Hp's drop, then it wears off and i reapply :)  by the time that wears off the mobs is half dead. now i can either reapply again or stop and melee with the huge beast in front of everyone, using debuffs like drowsy.  or i can just DoT until its dead without taking any damage. decent XP but there is often a little downtime while i med. but i just send all my tells, auction, and shouts ect.<br>
i am also working on other techniques as well, but i always get faster XP in a group, when the group is good :P<p>

Bogorden 12th lvl shaman  <br>
fennin ro <br>
