<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Wallster, wallster...<p>

Bards can kite.  The can kite very hard stuff with a lot of safty.  But i'd say wiz is the best kiter.  it's takes 15min for a level 37 bard to kite choon in Wk, but it takes me 40 secs at level 35 or so.  bonds of force, blast, blast, blast.  310 dd kills choon in 6 shots.  by the time choon falls right behind my back, i still have 2bub of mana.  i sit and med for 5 min, gtg again.<p>

now choon is a blue mob.  let's talk about even cons.  HGs i kill him everytime i see one in NK.  been doing that since level 33.  also been kiting griffons since level 31.  sure i run oom sometimes when i kite red mobs.  but i sit and med.  this is especially true when i kite in the plains after level 35.  i don't have to look at the spell book, for your information.  how do i outrun all the mobs i kite if bonds of force fails?  easy, i have sow on.  here is the trick, shout to pay for sow every 30min, cuz sow lasts for 40min.  what if there is no druid, shaman, ranger around?  i go to my bag and pull out a sow potion and drink it.  tip number 2: carry lots of sow potions on ya till u get jboots.  do i every use root nuke strategy anymore?  sometimes when i am in dungeon and on low to mid blues.<p>

and let me tell you, a druid is good kiter, but it's almost impossible for druids to kite yellow or red mobs without oom.  sure they can med too when kiting, i give them for that.<p>

