<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">On the issue of downtime versus time spent.  I am a level 22 druid(currently, I average a level a day when I play) and I take mobs that are 6 levels higher than me on average (right now being Aviak Harriers, level 27 but good nuff until next level when I switch to Avocets)  The thing that bugs me is the bard issue of time spent kiting a mob.  15 minutes is a long time.  I can kite a red mob for 15 minutes and still have full mana, just because I keep a stopwatch handy and count my seconds (kiting is an art btw, if you do it right = P). The secret is snare and DOT, run for 25 seconds, med for 26 seconds, stand up snare and dot again.  In the time I spend down medding, I med up the mana I used for casting stinging swarm and snare (I love 10 mana spells).  this keeps me at pretty much a full bar of mana.  Now if I get impatient, I will turn around when the mob is at half health and DD it like crazy, but if we are just talking straight no down time, I can kite a mob until it dies.  now doing this to mobs that are 5 levels higher than me takes about 15  minutes...  that puts us on par at least with Bards...  but you know what?  if I die in south Karana, I pop back to my bind spot right outside of the Lake Rathe zone... Bards either go to the Arena or back to Qeynos...  hmmm, then the time seems to be on the druids side again = P...<p>

Kiting is as useful as the user behind the keyboard is...  Any class for you if you know how to kite with it.  Nuff Said...<p>

Salicia Swiftfoot<br>
Druid in her 22+ Season<br>
Bertoxxulous</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
