<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">This is my point of view:<p>

Necro kitting is cool: Fear, dot and slow, send pet, refear. Short and easy, but sorta mean.<p>

Shaman kitting is ok: Debuff, root, dot, dot, dot, dot, root, med, same again, or start melee with nukes memmed... Fun.<p>

Druid kitting is crap: Snare, dot, nuke, run all over the zone, just the get out another nuke that might get resisted and therefor run again all over the zone, just the get out another nuke that might get resisted run again all over the zone, just the get out another nuke that might get resisted run again all over the zone, just the get out another nuke that might get resisted run again all over the zone, just the get out another nuke that might get resisted and therefor run again... Boring.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
