<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">Bards are better...druids are better...wizards are the BEST!!!<br>
  Whats up with all this mess?  Nobody has brought necros or mages up, did everyone forget them?  <br>
  Lets see, what does a necro have useful for kiting besides some of the most efficient dots in the game, the most dots, life to mana confersion, lifetap, fear, snare, root, DD's, feign death and a pet and heals for the pet.  Dang when i say that does anyone feel self concience?  They can pretty much take out anything they want these days, and if they cant well they can just feign death or let the pet tank while they run.<br>
  Mages on the other hand may be bad at "kiting" but besides having the second best DD's in the game, the best damage shields, and the most situation addaptable pets in the game...i would say they can hold thier own.  Put out a Earth pet with rune swords, damage shield the sucker and watch the mob chew away at its 3000 hps or so with a nasty damage sheild on.  If you get bored you can heal the pet or DD the mob occasionally.  Oh no!  the pet is dying, they just make another cause mages are the best at chain summoning also ;)<br>
  Every class can kite to some degree except the pure melees, its just a matter of how smart you are.  Plus who really cares about kiting when you want to get gear?  Yea i sure love having people in my group that have kited their whole lives... lol, when the whole group dies.  If you want real experience (not just the yellow stuff) you need to group with people and learn the class strengths and "rules of engagement" (great movie btw ;).  <br>
  Well i think im done with my rant, no offense peeps.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
